Eight people have died after two taxis and a truck collided in Leeugamka, in the Western Cape. For more on this, Devan Mugruan speaks to Southern Cape police spokesperson Malcolm Pojie. Courtesy #DStv403  JOHANNESBURG - Eight people have died in a collision between a truck and two taxis in the Karoo. Southern Cape police spokesperson Malcolm Pojie says mop-up operations are under way. He said preliminary investigations show that the truck was travelling towards Cape Town when it collided with two taxis. READ: Four die in Eastern Cape crash "We are investigating a culpable homicide [case] and we are busy with mopping-up operations," Pojie said. "It's a horrific accident." Pojie said the truck driver is in a critical condition and was transported to the Beaufort West provincial hospital.